ECLOGUE XII.

The twelfth Eclogue is an ‘aegloga moralissima', addressed to Louis XII. It was not included in the editions of the Buccolica printed at Paris in 1496(?), 1501. 1506. L. Thuasne (op. cit. i. 131) says it appeared in 1498, and Mlle. Pellechet (i. 154) includes an un— dated edition of it among the French Incunabula. It was printed at Strassburg in 1512 and in 1513. In one of these Strassburg editions, the title states that ‘Corydon ⁷ is Andrelinus himself—“ in qua Cory- don senex sub persona Fausti admonet Mopsum iuvenem ³³, etc. At line 218 ‘Corydon' professes to be 50 years old—which might have led one to set the poem about 1511 or 1512.
